French money supply , measured term M-3 , rose provisional one pct January falling 0.7 pct December , Bank France said .
M-3 main money supply aggregate used French monetary authority .
It joined second main money supply aggregate 1987 M-2 , rose provisional 1.2 pct January falling confirmed 0.9 pct December .
Calculated three-month moving average basis , M-3 rose 4.4 pct year-on-year quarter based December rising 5.4 pct quarter centred September .
The M-2 aggregate , centred three-month moving average , rose year-on-year four pct , within 1987 target range four six pct .
M-1 rose 2.5 pct 1.1 pct fall December .
M-1 measure note coin circulation plus sight deposit .
M-2 add short-term bank deposit M-3 add short-term deposit .
The central bank 's widest measure liquidity , L , rose 1.5 pct January one pct fall December .
The bank said money supply growth reflected net increase sight deposit renewed interest money market instrument .
